<P>
 Regarding the efforts of the Menendez defense team to suppress the showing of 
the Fox made-for-TV movie about their crimes: I can certainly sympathize with 
the defense's efforts to obtain an unbiased jury and agree that a 
pro-prosecution movie could indeed taint the jury pool. Perhaps the best 
solution here, as in other high-profile cases, would be to change the location 
of the trial. In fact, I would like to suggest a different venue. How about 
Singapore? 
