<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP EYE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 AND ONE MORE THING: "Buckshot LeFonque," due in July from Columbia, is the 
name of the new Branford Marsalis project -- a collaboration with DJ Premier of 
rap group Gang Starr that features appearances by poet Maya Angelou (reading "I 
Know Why the Caged Bird Sings"), Ruben Blades, the late Albert Collins and 
former Springsteen sidekick Nils Lofgren. The first single, "Breakfast at 
Denny's," is about the controversy over the restaurant chain's alleged racially 
discriminatory practices and incorporates part of a Jay Leno monologue. 
Buckshot LeFonque, by the way, was a pseudonym used by jazz great Cannonball 
Adderley on his independent projects. 
</P>
