<HEADLINE>
<P>
DON'T GIVE DETAILS ON THE TOAD CRAZE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I am writing to you regarding the April 19 article "A New Craze Hops Into Drug 
Culture" (toad smoking). 
</P>
<P>
 I find it incredibly irresponsible of you to publish this article purporting 
to illustrate, on the one hand, the dangers and cruelty of this "bizarre 
phenomenon," yet on the other hand, supplying each and every reader with an 
exacting description of which species to look for, where to look, how to 
excrete the substance from toads' glands, how to smoke it and the fair market 
street value for the illegal entrepreneur. 
</P>
<P>
 JULIA M. THOMPSON 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA050194-0082 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 037481 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
May 1, 1994, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Travel; Part L; Page 1; Column 1; Travel Desk 
</P>
