<P>
 Telephone ticket sales for one of the crown jewels of Europe's summer opera 
season -- the Glyndebourne Festival in Lewes, England -- begin Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Ticket prices for the season that opens May 28 range from about $15 to $150 
and include, for the first time, 40 standing-room tickets. Performances will 
take place in a new $50-million opera house. 
</P>
