DOING JULIAN JUSTICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 If I had never been to Julian, I certainly would not be inspired to go on the 
basis of your article ("Off-Season Apple Pie," April 10).It not only failed to 
mention the fascinating gold mine tour, but even failed to do justice to the 
historic Julian Hotel. I think the town is a perfect low-key weekend 
destination and certainly deserves better coverage. And whereas the restaurants 
may not be exactly gourmet, I think a writer might choose an establishment (or 
item on the menu) which would capture more of the local scene. 
</P>
<P>
 GEORGIA DI DONATO 
</P>
