<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIXON'S RETURN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Living across from Yorba Linda in the hills above Anaheim Hills, I 
experienced quite a phenomenon last Tuesday afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
 After watching the arrival of Richard Nixon's casket, along with his family on 
television at El Toro, I followed its route to Yorba Linda and along with it 
was quite a downpour. While it wasn't even raining here, all afternoon the eye 
of the storm, with hail, lightning and thunder, seemed to be right over Yorba 
Linda. 
</P>
<P>
 I couldn't help but feel that President Nixon was letting his presence be 
known and giving us his one last speech. 
</P>
<P>
 We will miss him. May he rest in peace. 
</P>
<P>
 BETTY BARR 
</P>
<P>
 Orange 
</P>
