<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; NEVADA GETS TO WAGNER AND BEATS TITANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton's Matt Wagner gave up seven runs on eight hits in six 
innings in the Titans' 7-2 loss to Nevada on Saturday at Titan Field. 
</P>
<P>
 The loss ended Wagner's 10-game winning streak, dropping him to 10-1. 
</P>
<P>
 The Titans (34-10, 11-5) managed only four hits off Wolf Pack starter John 
Patton (5-1), who struck out six in eight innings. Reliever Jason Rogers 
retired the side in order for Nevada in the ninth. 
</P>
<P>
 Titan shortstop Jack Jones had one hit and scored a run, and right fielder 
Mark Kotsay doubled for the Titans' only extra-base hit. 
</P>
<P>
 Center fielder Dante Powell walked, stole a base and scored the Titans' other 
run. 
</P>
<P>
 The loss drops Cal State Fullerton out of first place in the Big West, one 
game behind the Wolf Pack (34-7, 11-3). The Titans host the series finale at 1 
p.m. today. 
</P>
<P>
 In Golden State Athletic Conference baseball: 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California College 5-6, Concordia 3-8 -- Ryan Seidel was two for four 
with two doubles and an RBI and David Seeley was two for four with a home run 
for SCC (18-24, 8-9) in the first game. 
</P>
<P>
 Christopher Kindreich was three for four with two RBIs for Concordia (16-26-1, 
5-12) in the second game. 
</P>
<P>
 In Big West Conference softball: 
</P>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton 7-9, New Mexico State 1-0 -- Shannon Dolan's grand slam in 
the second game led the Titans (25-25, 14-9) to the sweep at home. Dolan, a 
junior catcher, had three hits and drove in six runs. 
</P>
