<HEADLINE>
<P>
DINGER FOILS HIS PURSUERS IN WINNING SAUGUS MAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RON STAPP, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Scott Dinger captured his third main event of the season with a victory in the 
Pro Stock oval feature race Saturday night at Saugus Speedway.  
</P>
<P>
 But it wasn't easy. 
</P>
<P>
 The Simi Valley resident started on the pole, but was shadowed by three cars 
for the entire 25 laps. 
</P>
<P>
 "There was a lot of pressure," Dinger said. "The car wasn't handling very 
well. It was hard to keep it under me." 
</P>
<P>
 That was primarily because Santa Clarita's Jeff Schrader was breathing down 
his neck.  
</P>
<P>
 Schrader moved past Gerrit Cromsigt of Pine Mountain Club on the sixth lap and 
was never more than half a car length behind for the final 19 laps. 
</P>
<P>
 Arleta's Brian Kelley provided similar pressure in third place, followed 
closely by Cromsigt, who finished fourth.  
</P>
<P>
 Dinger, 34, who entered the night with a 24-point lead over Richard Karvasek 
in the points standings, added a victory in the figure-eight trophy dash.  
</P>
<P>
 In the Mini Stock main event, Terry Limberopoulos of Bellflower moved past 
points leader Jeff McCall of Gardena on Lap 13 and cruised to his second 
feature victory in three starts. 
</P>
<P>
 McCall wound up second, with Robert Hynes of West Hills and Newbury Park's 
John Petsco finishing third and fourth. 
</P>
<P>
 Richard Lloyd of Gardena won the Mini Stock Racing Assn. main event. El 
Monte's Kenny Smith was second. 
</P>
</TEXT>
