<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA TRIUMPHS DESPITE EFFORTS OF OXNARD CATCHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Despite a record effort by Oxnard College catcher Robert Sanchez, Ventura 
defeated the Condors, 5-4, Saturday in a Western State Conference baseball 
game. 
</P>
<P>
 In the fourth inning, Sanchez gunned down three Ventura runners trying to 
steal second. 
</P>
<P>
 "That's a record that can be tied, but never broken," Ventura assistant Don 
Adams said. 
</P>
<P>
 Sanchez, a freshman, threw out four runners in the game. Ventura leads the 
conference with 86 stolen bases this season. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura (22-14, 11-9 in WSC games) jumped to a 5-1 lead and held on when Bob 
Patterson pitched out of a bases-loaded jam in the eighth inning en route to 
his first save. Craig Arnold pitched five shutout innings in relief for Oxnard 
(15-20, 9-12). 
</P>
</TEXT>
