<HEADLINE>
<P>
NORTH HILLS VA HOSPITAL HAS FULL ARRAY OF SERVICES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * I would like to clarify some points made by veterans and reporters who say 
the Sepulveda VA Medical Center in North Hills is closed and there is no 
transportation to the West Los Angeles VA Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Sepulveda's new mission is to provide a full array of outpatient and nursing 
home care to the veterans we serve.Inpatient services will be provided by the 
West Los Angeles center. 
</P>
<P>
 The Sepulveda VA outpatient program is fully operational. This includes 
medical, surgical, mental health, drug and alcohol abuse clinics. In addition, 
the 120-bed nursing home care unit will be opening soon. There is an active vet 
center on the medical center grounds. Research and education will continue to 
be important activities at Sepulveda. 
</P>
<P>
 The Sepulveda VA Medical Center is affiliated with UCLA and will continue to 
provide the most sophisticated health care available today with a staff of 
highly skilled physicians, nurses and allied health professionals using the 
most modern technology. 
</P>
<P>
 An urgent care section has been initiated here at Sepulveda and is open from 8 
a.m. to 11 p.m. daily, including Saturdays, Sundays and holidays. Veterans 
seeking care at the Sepulveda VA facility who need emergency hospitalization 
will be examined and transferred to the nearest private-sector hospital by 
ambulance. Veterans needing elective or non-urgent inpatient hospitalization 
are transported to the West Los Angeles center. 
</P>
<P>
 Sepulveda has been offering a wide range of specialty services to the veterans 
of the San Fernando Valley and the surrounding areas for more than 40 years. 
When the new state-of-the-art outpatient clinic is completed in December, 1995, 
it will further enhance these services.  
</P>
<P>
 PERRY C. NORMAN 
</P>
<P>
 Director 
</P>
<P>
 Department of Veterans 
</P>
<P>
 Affairs Medical Center 
</P>
<P>
 North Hills 
</P>
