<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTH: WATTS; AUTHOR HAIZLIP AT ROSE GARDEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Author Shirlee Taylor Haizlip will be on hand when the Watts Senior Center 
Rose Garden receives nationwide accreditation Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 The center's garden, at 1657 E. Century Blvd., was recently selected by All 
American Rose Selections to receive accreditation. There are 137 other rose 
gardens that have received similar recognition. All American Rose Selections is 
a Chicago-based nonprofit association that promotes rose research.  
</P>
<P>
 Haizlip, author of "The Sweeter the Juice," will speak at 11 a.m. on the 
importance of senior citizens passing on their histories to younger 
generations. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 564-9440. 
</P>
