<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: EAST: CITY TERRACE; YOUTH CLUB TO HONOR 3 AT AWARDS DINNER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Salesian Boys and Girls Club will honor three people for their work in 
East Los Angeles neighborhoods at its Award of Excellence Dinner on May 12. 
</P>
<P>
 Honoree Frank Villalobos is an architect who is active in Eastside issues and 
serves on the club's board of directors.Sister Jennie Lechtenberg founded 
People United to Enrich the Neighborhood Through Education (PUENTE), which 
provides job training, English as a Second Language classes and computer 
education for families in Boyle Heights. Artist George Yepes, who grew up as a 
member of the club, runs a free art academy for youths, who donate their works 
to nonprofit organizations. 
</P>
<P>
 The dinner will be at the Hotel Intercontinental, 251 S. Olive St. 
</P>
<P>
 The event also helps spread the word about the club's activities for local 
youths, said the Rev. Carmine Vairo, executive director. 
</P>
<P>
 The fund-raising dinner usually brings in about as much money as the annual 
February golf tournament, which this year netted $37,000.  
</P>
<P>
 Tickets are $125 each, with corporate tables available at various prices. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: Sharon Benoit at (818) 957-0913, or Vairo at (213) 263-8992 or 
(213) 268-4798. 
</P>
</TEXT>
