<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOTHER'S DAY BREAKFAST FOR SENIORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The seventh annual Young and the Wise Mother's Day Breakfast this Saturday at 
Lafayette Park is a chance for civic-minded young people to serve breakfast to 
older folks and let them know that their contributions to the community are 
appreciated. 
</P>
<P>
 The free event begins at 8:30 a.m. on the east side of the park and is 
sponsored by the Wilshire Center Community Involvement Assn. with the support 
of several other community organizations. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year, youths from the Bresee Foundation Youth Center, the YWCA, and the 
Wilshire and Rampart Explorers served breakfast to about 300 senior citizens. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: Urla Price, (213) 484-3716. 
</P>
