<P>
 El Pollo Loco acts: Ray Perry, chief operating officer of Irvine-based El 
Pollo Loco, thinks his restaurant chain will benefit from parent corporation 
Flagstar Cos. Inc.'s decision to sell its Canteen food and vending operations 
to Compass Group PLC. The sale, announced on Wednesday, "will allow Flagstar to 
reduce its debt and provide capital for growth, be it new restaurant growth or 
remodeling of restaurants," Perry said. 
</P>
<P>
 Perry is betting that some of the additional capital to be available at 
Spartanburg, S.C.-based Flagstar will flow through to El Pollo Loco. "Flagstar 
was never comfortable with the contract feeding and vending side of the 
business," Perry said. "The company has good leaders on the restaurant side, 
and this will let them concentrate on what they're best at." 
