make Golden West College's pep squad for football and basketball games -- she 
cannot hear, which means extra effort picking up the music cues. "It's 
important to let people know that deaf people can do anything," she says. . . . 
Actually, all who made the squad are lucky. Next year's squad was axed in a 
budget crunch. But after hearing some disappointment, President Philip Westin 
vows he'll find the money somewhere to keep it going. 
