<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; SHOTS ARE FIRED AT MEDICAL LABORATORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Authorities are looking for suspects in a drive-by shooting against a Ventura 
medical laboratory, the Ventura Police Department said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 About two dozen late-shift workers were on duty at the Mayo Medical Laboratory 
in the 1800 block of Palma Drive about 11:45 p.m. Friday, but no one was 
injured when several shots were fired into the rear of the building.  
</P>
<P>
 Police said the shooting was apparently one of a series of similar incidents 
against the company that are under investigation, but the Ventura Police 
Department spokesman would give no further details. 
</P>
<P>
 Representatives from Mayo Medical Laboratory would not comment on the 
shootings Saturday. SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</TEXT>
