<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; CITY TAKES SURVEY ON BUSINESS CONDITIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 More than one-third of Ventura businesses hired new employees last year, and 
just over a quarter say they intend to make more hires this year, according to 
a survey of local businesses.  
</P>
<P>
 The survey, conducted by the city and released last week, included 76 
businesses of varying size around Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 About two-thirds of the businesses surveyed have been in Ventura for 10 years 
or more. If they had the choice to relocate today, 57% of business owners 
surveyed said they would stay in Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 However, nearly one-third of the business owners said they do not find the 
city responsive enough to their problems.  
</P>
<P>
 Thirty-two percent of respondents told surveyors that if the city wanted to 
improve Ventura's business climate, it needs to work harder at being 
responsive. CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
