BRIEFLY; FELLOWSHIP: AT UCLA, 6 AWARDED GUGGENHEIMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nineteen University of California faculty and staff, including six from UCLA, 
have received prestigious Guggenheim Fellowships for outstanding work in their 
fields, UC officials announced this week. 
</P>
<P>
 The recipients from UCLA are Joyce Appleby, professor of history, for her work 
on careers, civil society and concepts of the nation between 1789 and 1829; 
Giorgio Buccallati, professor of history and the ancient Near East, for his 
work on Khana and the Amorites; William A. V. Clark, professor of geography, 
for study of international migration; Meg Cranston, art lecturer and an 
authority on sculpture; Mike Rose, lecturer in writing who focuses on public 
education, and Mary A. Rouse of the Center for Medieval and Renaissance 
Studies. 
