<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXAMINING L.A.'S MEANEST STREETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Times today takes a look at Los Angeles' most violent neighborhoods and 
examines strategies for turning the tide in these "hot target" districts, which 
last year reported the most murders, rapes, robberies and aggravated assaults 
in each of the LAPD's four bureaus. Section B 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
