<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: BEVERLY HILLS; SALTERS ARE NAMED CITIZENS OF YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By G. JEANETTE AVENT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Former Mayor Maxwell Salter and his wife, Janet, will be honored this week as 
Citizens of the Year by the Beverly Hills Chamber of Commerce. 
</P>
<P>
 The Salters will be recognized for their community service during the 
chamber's 41st annual Beverly Hills Ball on Friday at the Beverly Hilton Hotel. 
</P>
<P>
 Emceed by game show host Monty Hall, the event will also honor the president 
and 10 past presidents of the Academy of Motion Picture Arts & Sciences, which 
is based in Beverly Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Academy president Arthur Hiller, who has directed more than 30 movies, 
including "Love Story," will receive the chamber's Will Rogers Memorial Award. 
G. JEANETTE AVENT 
</P>
</TEXT>
