<HEADLINE>
<P>
HUNTINGTON BEACH MAN ARRESTED IN KIDNAPING; ABDUCTION: HE ALLEGEDLY DRAGGED A 
WOMAN INTO HIS CAR, MASTURBATED AS HE DROVE AND THEN RELEASED HER, POLICE SAID. 
HE WAS CAUGHT AFTER CALLING TO ASK IF HE COULD MEET HER AGAIN. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 35-year-old man was arrested after he allegedly dragged a woman into his 
car, masturbated a he drove for 10 minutes and then let her out of the car, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ken Dwayne Ingram of Huntington Beach was arrested Friday on suspicion of 
kidnaping and indecent exposure after he called the woman at work and asked to 
meet her again, Westminster police said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The abduction occurred when the 19-year-old woman was walking to work on Beach 
Boulevard, just south of the San Diego Freeway. Police said that Ingram pulled 
alongside her in a beige Toyota about 8:30 p.m. Friday. Believing the man 
wanted to ask her a question, the woman walked to the car, Sgt. Dwight Moore 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 That was when the driver pulled her into the passenger seat and drove to a 
nearby freeway on-ramp, Moore said. As he drove, the man masturbated and asked 
the woman -- whose name was not released -- questions about herself, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man, who called himself Kenny, then drove the woman to work near the site 
where he picked her up, authorities said. Ingram allegedly called the woman at 
work about two hours later and asked if he could meet her. She agreed. 
</P>
<P>
 Wha Ingram did not know was that the woman called Westminster police, who set 
up surveillance in the area, authorities said. When Ingram arrived in a silver 
Nissan, police arrested him. 
</P>
<P>
 A notebook found in his possession indicates he may have had similar 
encounters with other women, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ingram was booked at the Orange County Jail in lieu of $50,000 bail, jail 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone with information about similar incidents is asked to contact 
Westminster Police Investigator Tom Green at (714) 898-3315, Ext. 306. 
</P>
</TEXT>
